  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nUsing Qute `asHtmlAttributes` is escaping the quotes in the output:\r\n```html\r\n<form action=\"{it}\" method=\"{method ?: 'POST'}\" {_args.skip('method', 'it').asHtmlAttributes}>\r\n {#authenticityToken/}\r\n {nested-content}\r\n</form>\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nThe workaround is to use: `asHtmlAttributes.safe`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```html\r\n<form action=\"/HtmxApp/save/6\" method=\"POST\" hx-put=\"/HtmxApp/save/6\" hx-swap=\"&quot;outerHTML&quot;\" hx-target=\"this\">\r\n```\r\n\r\n**I believe the value (inside the quote) should be escaped**\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n```html\r\n<form action=\"/HtmxApp/save/6\" method=\"POST\" hx-put=\"&quot;/HtmxApp/save/6&quot;\" hx-swap=\"&quot;outerHTML&quot;\" hx-target=\"&quot;this&quot;\"\r\n\">\r\n```\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n3.6.5\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
